Type 'make' to compile the code.

Place an LB2D_Prime velocity dat file in the dat folder and edit it as follows:
Add one line at the top of the file containing LX followed by LY. See the
example ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat .

Then run ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat

It will create an lic_in.bmp file which is the input texture used to generate
the flow lines pattern that will be output in lic.bmp .

Experiment with

  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 1
  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 2
  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 3
  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 4
  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 5
  ./lic.exe ./dat/u299x299_frame0036_subs00.dat 6

to get the following different colors/textures:

  1  Black and white noise.
  2  Color noise.
  3  Velocity based. Blue/green frame with white-noise fill.
  4  Velocity based. Red/green noise.
  5  Red/Green noise frame with blue noise fill.
  6  Velocity based. Blue/Green
